[2] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro): military horses, pre-Olympic event
Date: Tue 28 Jul 2015
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.JW, edited]
http://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/casos-de-mormo-pulam-para-17-governo-vai-sacrificar-os-cavalos-16999787


The Ministry of Agriculture confirmed on [Tue 28 Jul 2015] that there are 17 diagnosed cases of horses with glanders, not including the 2 diagnosed earlier. All the animals are quarantined in Cananea Island, in Sao Paulo, and will be used for studies of the disease before being terminated. Glanders is a deadly disease for horses, and easily transmitted among animals, through contact with contaminated secretions, urine or feces, for example. Humans can also be infected by contact with contaminated excretions as this is a zoonotic disease. [see below. - Mod>RNA]

A week before the Equestrian test event for the Rio 2016 Games, scheduled for 6 Aug 2015, the outbreak can increase, as there are hundreds of horses undergoing tests after finding an outbreak in the Military Deodoro complex sector 4. This area, the Army Equitation School, is located about 550 m [0.35 mi] from the Olympic Equestrian Centre (COH), where the Olympic tournament will be held next year [2016], for the best horses in the world.

The federal agency did not say how many of the 17 horses isolated on the island are from Deodoro, but there are animals from Rio and other states. The ministry said that despite the new cases, the picture is not epidemic or a threat to health security of Olympic events -- the COH is in sanitary isolation since February [2015]. Next week [week of 3 Aug 2015], 72 international observers will come to Rio de Janeiro to follow the test event, between horsemen, members of the International Equestrian Federation (FEI), and equestrian confederations from several countries. Besides getting information about the track details and facilities, the conditions of biosecurity sanitary isolation will be investigated.

The glanders outbreak exposes the fragility of Brazilian sanitary control for the disease. As the national laboratories have not got an ISO certificate for the diagnosis of glanders, the federal government had to send samples of 584 horses from Deodoro to Germany. The Ministry of Agriculture says it is negotiating the delivery of results in the "shortest possible time".

As 14 horses of Deodoro sector 4, the focus of glanders, participated in competitions of the Brazilian Equestrian Society in April [2015], the most traditional country club, located in Lagoa Rodrigo de Freitas [Rio de Janeiro], was closed on the night of [Mon 27 Jul 2015] so that their horses could be examined. The direction of the Equestrian Society reported that their animals are [already] subjected to bimonthly glanders tests and there has never been a diagnosis of glanders on the site. The activities and internal tournaments of the club are continuing in spite of the prohibition of entry and exit of horses. Only in cases of need for surgery will horses be allowed to leave the grounds.

[Byline: Miguel Caballero]

